    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>The String I had to convert to a URI was a local file path, but without the <code>file://</code> prefix. So even</p>\n<pre><code> Uri.parse(Uri.decode(STRING));\n</code></pre>\n<p>resulted in <code>FileNotFoundException: No content provider</code> (see also <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3288619/what-to-do-when-java-io-filenotfoundexception-no-content-provider\">this question</a>).\nI got a valid URI by first creating a <code>File</code> object i.e.:</p>\n<pre><code>Uri myUri = Uri.fromFile(new File(STRING));\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
